title: One Man Dies In Two Vehicle Crash In Day County
text:
One Man Dies In Two Vehicle Crash In Day County October 25, 2015, 2:50 PM ANDOVER, SD - 
One man is dead after a two-vehicle crash east of Andover, South Dakota. 
Around 12:30 a.m Sunday, a 50-year-old man was driving his mini-van eastbound in the right westbound lane on US Highway 12 when it struck an RV traveling westbound in the same lane. 
Five people were inside the RV; only one person received minor injuries. The driver of the mini-van was pronounced dead at the scene. 
Debris from the crash site resulted in another crash when a car hit a tire that had come off the RV. The two people in the vehicle suffered non-life threatening injuries. Highway Patrol closed down the westbound lanes of US Highway 12 for over four hours. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
